article.headline: Middle Tennessee 83, Louisiana-Lafayette 76
article.story: MURFREESBORO, Tenn. -- Kevin Kanaskie scored 18 points and Middle Tennessee State held off Louisiana-Lafayette 83-76 on Thursday night. Leading 66-52 with 6:19 left, the Blue Raiders (13-8, 7-3 Sun Belt Conference) made 17 of 24 free throws -- but no field goals -- the rest of the game, but the Ragin' Cajuns could get no closer than six. Louisiana-Lafayette (7-13, 4-5) is 1-8 on the road this season. Middle Tennessee State was 27 of 36 from the foul line for the game. The Blue Raiders scored no points in the final 3:52 of the first half, but still led 33-30 at halftime. Kanaskie was 3 of 5 from the field and 10 of 10 from the stripe for the Blue Raiders. Montarrio Haddock added 15 points, Calvin O'Neil and Demetrius Green had 14 apiece and Desmond Yates scored 11. Courtney Wallace had 15 points, Ryan McCoy 14 and Travis Bureau 11 for the Ragin' Cajuns.
